1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:05,880
[Azuelo] We will patrol the city
to prevent any crime.

2
00:00:05,964 --> 00:00:08,174
- Sir, whose idea was this?
- General Carillo's.

3
00:00:08,258 --> 00:00:11,386
[Azuelo] <i>I want all of you</i>
<i>to be on your best game</i>

4
00:00:11,469 --> 00:00:13,513
<i>when the Japanese investors arrive.</i>

5
00:00:13,596 --> 00:00:15,640
- What do you think he's up to?
- I don't know.

6
00:00:15,724 --> 00:00:17,183
We have to be vigilant.

7
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:19,561
[Marcus] <i>I can sense</i>
<i>that he's up to something.</i>

8
00:00:19,644 --> 00:00:22,063
[Marcus] <i>In order to make</i>
<i>our patrol more efficient,</i>

9
00:00:22,147 --> 00:00:23,606
<i>we will do a buddy system.</i>

10
00:00:23,690 --> 00:00:25,024
<i>Sabdani, you're with me.</i>

11
00:00:25,108 --> 00:00:26,735
[Espina] <i>I'll partner up</i>
<i>with Agent Angeles.</i>

12
00:00:26,818 --> 00:00:28,278
Why did you make me your partner, huh?

13
00:00:28,361 --> 00:00:29,821
Is there a problem, Agent Angeles?

14
00:00:29,904 --> 00:00:31,740
I can manage. I don't need your help.

15
00:00:31,823 --> 00:00:33,241
[Espina] <i>Is it me you hate?</i>

16
00:00:33,324 --> 00:00:35,702
<i>Or is it the thought</i>
<i>of seeking help from others</i>

17
00:00:35,785 --> 00:00:37,746
<i>and appearing weak?</i>

18
00:00:37,829 --> 00:00:39,873
<i>There will come a time</i>
<i>when you will feel weak.</i>

19
00:00:39,956 --> 00:00:42,333
<i>And that's okay because</i>
<i>that's just how humans are.</i>

20
00:00:42,417 --> 00:00:43,585
<i>We get tired sometimes.</i>

21
00:00:43,668 --> 00:00:44,627
<i>But remember,</i>

22
00:00:44,711 --> 00:00:47,130
<i>feeling weak isn't something</i>
<i>to be ashamed of.</i>

23
00:00:47,213 --> 00:00:48,715
[Lara] <i>So, why are you doing this?</i>

24
00:00:48,798 --> 00:00:52,218
Do we need to have a reason
to show kindness?

25
00:00:52,302 --> 00:00:53,678
[Espina] <i>I just wanted to make you smile.</i>

26
00:00:53,762 --> 00:00:56,222
<i>I hope you're not an accomplice, Lara.</i>

27
00:00:56,306 --> 00:00:57,807
<i>I don't want you to get dragged into this.</i>

28
00:00:57,891 --> 00:00:59,184
- [Raquel] <i>General.</i>
- [Manuel] <i>Hmm?</i>

29
00:00:59,267 --> 00:01:01,144
- [Raquel] <i>The car is ready.</i>
- [Manuel] <i>Mm-hmm.</i>

30
00:01:01,227 --> 00:01:06,441
[in English] This is going to be
the best day of my life!

31
00:01:06,524 --> 00:01:08,693
[organizer, in English] <i>Welcome</i>
<i>to the Philippines, gentlemen.</i>

32
00:01:08,777 --> 00:01:11,404
[in English] We are very pleased
to be here for this summit.

33
00:01:11,488 --> 00:01:13,782
[Manuel, in English]
<i>This is Task Force Alpha.</i>

34
00:01:13,865 --> 00:01:17,285
[in English] <i>They will personally</i>
<i>be in charge</i>

35
00:01:17,368 --> 00:01:20,580
<i>of your security</i>
<i>and protection for the whole day.</i>

36
00:01:20,663 --> 00:01:25,043
What scheme are you
cooking up now, General Carillo?

37
00:01:25,126 --> 00:01:28,379
[in English] Later, I will guide you
through the sanctuary's trail,

38
00:01:28,463 --> 00:01:31,591
but for now, please enjoy the view.

39
00:01:35,512 --> 00:01:38,348
[tense music playing]

40
00:01:41,059 --> 00:01:47,315
[mysterious theme music playing]

41
00:01:56,282 --> 00:02:03,039
[stirring music playing]

42
00:02:58,678 --> 00:03:04,684
- [foreboding music playing]
- [camera shutters clicking]

43
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:23,953
The summit for a major
investment agreement

44
00:03:24,037 --> 00:03:27,582
between Japanese investors
and Filipino businessmen

45
00:03:27,665 --> 00:03:29,000
has officially started.

46
00:03:29,083 --> 00:03:32,128
It is an agreement
that will boost the economy

47
00:03:32,211 --> 00:03:35,298
and strengthen the relationship
of the two countries.

48
00:03:35,381 --> 00:03:40,178
[thrilling music playing]

49
00:03:40,261 --> 00:03:43,097
Guys, this is historic for our country!

50
00:03:43,181 --> 00:03:45,308
This will help our economy a lot.

51
00:03:45,391 --> 00:03:49,687
Just think about the billions
of pesos that will be invested

52
00:03:49,771 --> 00:03:52,273
and the thousands of jobs

53
00:03:52,357 --> 00:03:55,568
that will be available
for ordinary Filipinos.

54
00:03:55,652 --> 00:03:57,987
You know, I'm very annoyed

55
00:03:58,071 --> 00:04:00,740
at those bashers and troll farms

56
00:04:00,823 --> 00:04:04,619
that keep spreading hate
and negative comments.

57
00:04:04,702 --> 00:04:06,037
They were like, "Blah, blah, blah."

58
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:07,664
They keep saying a lot of things.

59
00:04:07,747 --> 00:04:10,291
You see, we should help each other up,

60
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:12,001
not pull each other down.

61
00:04:12,085 --> 00:04:12,961
Enough with that attitude, okay?

62
00:04:13,044 --> 00:04:15,171
<i>Everyone's talking about the Phil-Japan</i>

63
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:17,590
<i>MiraiKona Economic Summit.</i>

64
00:04:17,674 --> 00:04:20,218
<i>What can we expect from this?</i>

65
00:04:20,301 --> 00:04:26,683
<i>Well, I'm sure they'll discuss</i>
<i>important business proposals</i>

66
00:04:26,766 --> 00:04:28,476
<i>involving infrastructure,</i>

67
00:04:28,559 --> 00:04:31,729
technology, and renewable energy.

68
00:04:31,813 --> 00:04:35,775
Having this agreement signed
will strengthen our economy.

69
00:04:35,858 --> 00:04:38,903
Our country will receive
billions of pesos in investment.

70
00:04:38,987 --> 00:04:41,364
That is, if the money goes
to where it's supposed to be

71
00:04:41,447 --> 00:04:44,284
and not in someone's pocket.

72
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:48,705
Yes, there are lots of corru--

73
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:50,290
[coughs] Thieves.

74
00:04:50,373 --> 00:04:53,251
That is why many are hoping and praying

75
00:04:53,334 --> 00:04:55,920
for the success of this investment deal.

76
00:04:56,004 --> 00:04:59,424
It is also expected to provide
thousands of jobs

77
00:04:59,507 --> 00:05:01,134
to Filipino workers.

78
00:05:01,217 --> 00:05:05,179
Task Force Alpha is also here
to ensure the security

79
00:05:05,263 --> 00:05:06,848
of everyone here at the summit.

80
00:05:06,931 --> 00:05:10,351
Oh my! There's the Task Force Alpha.

81
00:05:10,435 --> 00:05:12,312
[Peter] Look at them.

82
00:05:13,187 --> 00:05:16,607
[brooding music playing]

83
00:05:16,691 --> 00:05:19,027
Look, there's Sir Marcus.

84
00:05:19,110 --> 00:05:20,611
[smacks lips] Stop it.

85
00:05:20,695 --> 00:05:22,989
- [Gracia] Ow.
- [Peter mutters]

86
00:05:23,072 --> 00:05:24,365
- [Gracia] That's my uniform.
- [Peter] He's so handsome.

87
00:05:24,449 --> 00:05:25,825
[Gracia chuckles]

88
00:05:26,743 --> 00:05:33,166
[camera shutters clicking]

89
00:06:14,290 --> 00:06:15,583
[host, in English] Welcome!

90
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:18,503
[in English] Welcome
to the historic Phil-Japan

91
00:06:18,586 --> 00:06:21,130
MiraiKona Economic Summit.

92
00:06:21,214 --> 00:06:22,673
[in English] Today,
we are not just witnessing

93
00:06:22,757 --> 00:06:24,467
a meeting of great minds,

94
00:06:24,550 --> 00:06:27,095
but the binding of a partnership
filled with massive

95
00:06:27,178 --> 00:06:30,306
and big opportunities
for both our nations.

96
00:06:30,389 --> 00:06:32,308
[in English] Opportunities
that will redefine

97
00:06:32,391 --> 00:06:35,228
our shared economic landscapes
for decades to come.

98
00:06:35,311 --> 00:06:38,898
And through the decades
of our shared diplomatic friendship,

99
00:06:38,981 --> 00:06:42,527
it has proven that
the Philippines and Japan…

100
00:06:43,236 --> 00:06:46,322
I still don't know
what General Carillo is planning.

101
00:06:46,405 --> 00:06:49,408
[host continues talking indistinctly]

102
00:06:49,492 --> 00:06:51,410
Let's just keep watching him.

103
00:06:51,494 --> 00:06:52,745
[host, in English] …and share with you
those three things.

104
00:06:52,829 --> 00:06:54,997
[in English] Number one,
foreign direct investment.

105
00:06:55,081 --> 00:06:57,333
[in English] Number two,
sustainable development.

106
00:06:57,416 --> 00:07:00,920
[in English] And number three,
cutting-edge technological enhancements.

107
00:07:01,003 --> 00:07:04,382
[in English] I assure you that we
are standing on a golden era

108
00:07:04,465 --> 00:07:05,716
of innovation.

109
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,760
- So let this summit serve here today…
- [Manuel sighs]

110
00:07:07,844 --> 00:07:10,346
- [ManueL] Marcus.
- Sir.

111
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:11,889
- [Manuel] Carry on.
- [host] …local industries…

112
00:07:13,057 --> 00:07:15,601
Welcome back to the service.

113
00:07:15,685 --> 00:07:18,980
[in English] I hope you've come
to your senses, young man.

114
00:07:19,063 --> 00:07:24,110
Try not to be so reckless this time.

115
00:07:25,862 --> 00:07:26,988
[in English] Yes, sir.

116
00:07:28,448 --> 00:07:30,116
I'm a lot more cautious now.

117
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:33,453
Hmm… As you should.

118
00:07:33,953 --> 00:07:36,456
[in English] Don't make
the same mistake twice.

119
00:07:37,039 --> 00:07:39,876
Getting your badge back
could just be luck.

120
00:07:41,752 --> 00:07:42,587
[in English] Yes, sir.

121
00:07:42,670 --> 00:07:47,216
[tense music playing]

122
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:48,301
Sir.

123
00:07:52,763 --> 00:07:57,310
Agent Reyes took Datu Rahman
during an official operation.

124
00:07:58,519 --> 00:08:03,065
He did this under my command
and supervision, sir.

125
00:08:04,275 --> 00:08:10,323
[tense music continues]

126
00:08:10,406 --> 00:08:11,449
[scoffs]

127
00:08:21,876 --> 00:08:23,419
- [Usman] Sir.
- [Marcus] Sir.

128
00:08:27,089 --> 00:08:30,635
I think General Carillo
is planning something.

129
00:08:31,302 --> 00:08:34,263
Espina and I both think
he's going to make his move here.

130
00:08:37,558 --> 00:08:40,394
He's planning something? Here?

131
00:08:40,937 --> 00:08:43,022
Why would he do it here?

132
00:08:43,105 --> 00:08:44,815
To sabotage the deal?

133
00:08:45,775 --> 00:08:47,527
To undermine the government?

134
00:08:48,027 --> 00:08:50,279
To create destabilization?

135
00:08:50,363 --> 00:08:53,407
What for? So he could seize power?

136
00:08:53,491 --> 00:08:59,205
[tense music continues]

137
00:09:04,252 --> 00:09:06,546
Just drop it, Agent Reyes.

138
00:09:07,463 --> 00:09:08,381
[in English] Goddammit.

139
00:09:21,769 --> 00:09:26,649
[tense music intensifies]

140
00:09:26,732 --> 00:09:29,986
[Marcus] <i>Is that your plan,</i>
<i>General Carillo?</i>

141
00:09:42,331 --> 00:09:43,916
[in English] From the secretary

142
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,419
of the Department of Economic
Development and Industry,

143
00:09:46,502 --> 00:09:48,462
let us give a big round of applause

144
00:09:48,546 --> 00:09:51,299
for Secretary Alex V. Crisologo.

145
00:09:51,382 --> 00:09:56,637
[applause]

146
00:09:56,721 --> 00:09:58,598
- Yay! [laughs]
- [clapping]

147
00:09:58,681 --> 00:10:00,141
- Yay!
- Yes!

148
00:10:01,225 --> 00:10:02,059
[woman] Yes.

149
00:10:02,143 --> 00:10:05,229
I'm glad the investment
is pushing through.

150
00:10:05,313 --> 00:10:06,272
I know, right?

151
00:10:06,355 --> 00:10:07,857
I hope they get started right away.

152
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:10,901
And I hope our country continues to grow.

153
00:10:10,985 --> 00:10:14,614
- [in Arabic] God willing!
- [all, in Arabic] God willing!

154
00:10:15,990 --> 00:10:16,866
Thank goodness.

155
00:10:16,949 --> 00:10:19,243
Our economy is finally going to grow.

156
00:10:19,952 --> 00:10:21,454
[in Arabic] Praise be to God.

157
00:10:21,537 --> 00:10:24,457
[stirring music playing]

158
00:10:24,540 --> 00:10:27,460
[man on video, in English]
<i>Our blueprint for the coming years…</i>

159
00:10:28,252 --> 00:10:33,883
<i>…focuses heavily on smart city development</i>

160
00:10:33,966 --> 00:10:37,720
<i>and high-impact infrastructure projects</i>

161
00:10:38,304 --> 00:10:41,849
<i>by integrating Japanese</i>
<i>technical expertise with Fili…</i>

162
00:10:41,932 --> 00:10:44,894
[stirring music continues]

163
00:10:44,977 --> 00:10:46,854
[in Japanese] Hello, everyone!

164
00:10:47,355 --> 00:10:50,733
[in Japanese] Please look this way.

165
00:10:50,816 --> 00:10:54,987
[in English] This place became
a national park in 1995.

166
00:10:55,571 --> 00:10:58,324
[in Japanese] Hello, everyone!

167
00:10:58,407 --> 00:10:59,992
[in Japanese] We're
in the Philippines right now!

168
00:11:00,076 --> 00:11:06,123
[in Japanese] Look, everyone.
This bus is full of Japanese tourists!

169
00:11:06,207 --> 00:11:10,753
[unsettling music playing]

170
00:11:41,242 --> 00:11:44,412
[in English] And through
this strategic partnership,

171
00:11:44,495 --> 00:11:47,706
we are opening doors
to sustainable infrastructure…

172
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:49,625
[phone buzzing]

173
00:11:50,543 --> 00:11:53,462
…innovative technology transfers…

174
00:11:54,046 --> 00:11:55,423
[in Japanese] Look, everyone.

175
00:11:55,506 --> 00:11:59,885
[in Japanese] This bus
is full of Japanese tourists!

176
00:11:59,969 --> 00:12:01,011
[in Japanese] Mom!

177
00:12:03,347 --> 00:12:06,142
[in Japanese] Oh, Yui!
Your dad's watching!

178
00:12:06,225 --> 00:12:07,268
[Yui, in Japanese] <i>Really?</i>

179
00:12:07,351 --> 00:12:09,353
[in Japanese] <i>Dad's working hard</i>
<i>at the summit right now!</i>

180
00:12:09,437 --> 00:12:10,354
[in Japanese] <i>Are you watching?</i>

181
00:12:10,438 --> 00:12:12,606
- [in Japanese] <i>Oh, you really are!</i>
- [in Japanese] Thank you!

182
00:12:12,690 --> 00:12:14,150
[in Japanese] Keep up the good work!

183
00:12:14,233 --> 00:12:15,359
[giggling]

184
00:12:15,443 --> 00:12:16,861
- Bye!
- [giggles]

185
00:12:16,944 --> 00:12:21,782
[unsettling music intensifies]

186
00:12:39,175 --> 00:12:40,009
‪[inaudible]

187
00:12:45,681 --> 00:12:48,976
This is what I meant.

188
00:12:55,232 --> 00:12:57,526
[Jalil] <i>Are you working</i>
<i>with General Carillo?</i>

189
00:12:58,360 --> 00:12:59,361
<i>If you are,</i>

190
00:13:00,404 --> 00:13:02,239
<i>what kind of chaos are you planning?</i>

191
00:13:02,323 --> 00:13:08,162
[unsettling music continues]

192
00:13:09,371 --> 00:13:10,331
Sir.

193
00:13:11,540 --> 00:13:13,792
You've been glaring at them.

194
00:13:13,876 --> 00:13:15,211
What's wrong?

195
00:13:18,005 --> 00:13:21,675
Nothing, Domingo.
Just keep your eyes open.

196
00:13:23,552 --> 00:13:24,428
We have to be careful.

197
00:13:27,556 --> 00:13:28,724
[in English] Definitely, sir.

198
00:13:29,808 --> 00:13:30,726
I'll go back now.

199
00:13:30,809 --> 00:13:34,855
[unsettling music continues]

200
00:13:54,750 --> 00:14:00,130
[unsettling music continues]

201
00:14:00,214 --> 00:14:01,674
[Yui, in Japanese]
Keep up the good work, Dad.

202
00:14:01,757 --> 00:14:02,591
Bye!

203
00:14:06,470 --> 00:14:08,597
[timer beeping]

204
00:14:08,681 --> 00:14:13,310
[tourists talking indistinctly
in Japanese]

205
00:14:15,729 --> 00:14:19,608
[tourists cheering, clapping]

206
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:20,526
[door lock switch beeps]

207
00:14:21,443 --> 00:14:24,613
[tourist talking indistinctly]

208
00:14:25,781 --> 00:14:26,949
[in Japanese] What happened?

209
00:14:29,159 --> 00:14:30,744
Sit down! Hurry!

210
00:14:30,828 --> 00:14:32,037
[Benny] Sit down!

211
00:14:32,121 --> 00:14:37,042
[clamoring, whimpering]

212
00:14:37,126 --> 00:14:38,127
[in Japanese] Hurry up!

213
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:40,254
[in Japanese] Sit down!

214
00:14:41,422 --> 00:14:42,756
[in Japanese] From now on,

215
00:14:43,841 --> 00:14:48,929
you are our hostages!

216
00:14:49,013 --> 00:14:52,850
[crying, whimpering]

217
00:14:52,933 --> 00:14:55,978
[in Japanese] Cooperate with us.

218
00:14:56,478 --> 00:14:57,521
Shh!

219
00:14:57,605 --> 00:15:02,067
[in Japanese] Those
who don't cooperate will die.

220
00:15:02,151 --> 00:15:03,235
[in Japanese] Do you understand?!

221
00:15:03,319 --> 00:15:07,489
[crying, whimpering]

222
00:15:07,573 --> 00:15:08,949
[in Japanese] Do you understand?!

223
00:15:09,033 --> 00:15:15,080
[hostages crying]

224
00:15:16,081 --> 00:15:21,962
[tense music continues]

225
00:15:31,096 --> 00:15:32,640
You secure the perimeter.

226
00:15:32,723 --> 00:15:34,183
[phone dings]

227
00:15:38,479 --> 00:15:39,313
[in English] Dismissed.

228
00:15:40,105 --> 00:15:43,359
[grim music playing]

229
00:15:49,448 --> 00:15:50,741
It's begun.

230
00:15:50,824 --> 00:15:51,742
[dramatic sting]

231
00:15:58,999 --> 00:16:01,835
[woman in Japanese] I'm scared.

232
00:16:01,919 --> 00:16:03,879
[hostages crying, begging]

233
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:05,673
[in Japanese] Please, stop!

234
00:16:08,342 --> 00:16:10,469
[crying]

235
00:16:12,888 --> 00:16:14,139
[yells]

236
00:16:14,223 --> 00:16:15,307
- [kick lands]
- [hostages scream]

237
00:16:15,391 --> 00:16:16,558
[gunshot]

238
00:16:17,226 --> 00:16:19,979
- [all screaming]
- No one else move!

239
00:16:21,271 --> 00:16:22,982
- Huh!
- [in Japanese] Sit down!

240
00:16:23,065 --> 00:16:24,692
Did you hear that gunshot?

241
00:16:24,775 --> 00:16:26,568
It's that way. Let's check it out.

242
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:30,114
[suspenseful music playing]

243
00:16:30,197 --> 00:16:31,532
[hostage, in Japanese] Please…

244
00:16:32,366 --> 00:16:34,076
[crying]

245
00:16:38,497 --> 00:16:39,748
- [gunshot]
- [grunts]

246
00:16:40,290 --> 00:16:41,917
[police 1] Come on. Hurry up.

247
00:16:42,459 --> 00:16:43,961
Let's go.

248
00:16:48,966 --> 00:16:51,051
DAD, HELP US, PLEASE!

249
00:16:51,135 --> 00:16:52,845
[in English] Control, base. Control, base.

250
00:16:52,928 --> 00:16:54,138
We need backup.

251
00:16:54,221 --> 00:16:57,474
There's a hostage-taking
at San Aurelio Street.

252
00:16:57,558 --> 00:16:59,059
There are a lot of civilians.

253
00:17:00,769 --> 00:17:03,981
[in English] So, I guess this is a sign
of a good partnership.

254
00:17:10,070 --> 00:17:14,116
[all applaud]

255
00:17:14,825 --> 00:17:17,453
[suspenseful music continues]

256
00:17:37,056 --> 00:17:39,016
[phone dings]

257
00:17:43,228 --> 00:17:44,521
[pings]

258
00:17:44,605 --> 00:17:46,648
DAD, HELP US, PLEASE!

259
00:17:51,528 --> 00:17:53,113
[line rings]

260
00:17:57,076 --> 00:18:02,873
[suspenseful music continues]

261
00:18:07,211 --> 00:18:09,463
LIVE STREAM: CENTRAL CITY EXPRESS
TRANSPORTATION SYSTEM IN EMERGENCY

262
00:18:21,683 --> 00:18:23,310
[in Japanese] Please pass this through!

263
00:18:23,393 --> 00:18:25,020
[in Japanese] Please pass this through!

264
00:18:26,063 --> 00:18:31,485
[grim music playing]

265
00:18:31,568 --> 00:18:32,945
[dramatic sting]

266
00:18:33,529 --> 00:18:35,239
- [keyboard clacking]
- [digital trilling]

267
00:18:36,365 --> 00:18:38,575
- Ma'am!
- What happened?

268
00:18:38,659 --> 00:18:39,701
Flash it on-screen.

269
00:18:42,579 --> 00:18:43,997
[dramatic sting]

270
00:18:47,084 --> 00:18:51,839
[tense music playing]

271
00:18:53,882 --> 00:18:55,926
[Mr. Konno, in Japanese] My family!

272
00:18:56,009 --> 00:18:57,636
[Japanese delegate, in Japanese]
What's happening?

273
00:18:57,719 --> 00:18:58,846
[in English] What's wrong?
What's happening?

274
00:18:58,929 --> 00:19:00,305
[Japanese delegate, in Japanese]
Are you sure?

275
00:19:01,932 --> 00:19:02,891
[screaming on bus]

276
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:04,268
Oh…

277
00:19:05,561 --> 00:19:06,895
[camera shutters clicking]

278
00:19:06,979 --> 00:19:09,857
[hostages crying on video]

279
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:14,903
[in Japanese] <i>We are at</i>

280
00:19:14,987 --> 00:19:16,363
<i>San Aurelio Street.</i>

281
00:19:16,446 --> 00:19:17,531
Yui!

282
00:19:17,614 --> 00:19:19,908
[in English] That's my wife
and my daughter!

283
00:19:20,701 --> 00:19:21,869
Yui!

284
00:19:22,452 --> 00:19:23,495
Yui!

285
00:19:25,497 --> 00:19:27,249
[in English] Goddammit!

286
00:19:29,084 --> 00:19:31,879
Agent Reyes's hunch was right!

287
00:19:31,962 --> 00:19:35,799
[tense music continues]

288
00:19:44,099 --> 00:19:46,268
[in English] That's my wife and daughter!

289
00:19:47,186 --> 00:19:49,980
- [Mr. Konno gasping]
- [in English] Calm down, calm down.

290
00:19:50,063 --> 00:19:52,482
[Mr. Konno gasps, whimpers]

291
00:19:53,025 --> 00:19:54,276
[in English] Get a chair.

292
00:19:54,359 --> 00:19:56,570
[in English] Get some water. Get a chair.

293
00:19:56,653 --> 00:19:57,779
- Mr. Konno.
- [in English] They'll be alright.

294
00:19:57,863 --> 00:20:00,324
- [pen clicking]
- [digital trilling]

295
00:20:00,407 --> 00:20:01,241
‪[inaudible]

296
00:20:05,621 --> 00:20:08,665
[clicking faster]

297
00:20:13,253 --> 00:20:14,755
Sir, we have to save them.

298
00:20:14,838 --> 00:20:16,465
[Manuel] What are you waiting for?!

299
00:20:16,548 --> 00:20:18,717
Go! Save them!

300
00:20:20,469 --> 00:20:21,303
‪[music intensifies]

301
00:20:29,144 --> 00:20:31,980
[in English] Set to location. Move. Move!

302
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:33,190
- [radio beeps]
- [Espina] <i>Team.</i>

303
00:20:34,691 --> 00:20:37,236
There's a hostage-taking situation
at San Aurelio Street.

304
00:20:40,072 --> 00:20:42,741
[in English] All units,
gather at the main exit point.

305
00:20:42,824 --> 00:20:44,201
[in English] We move out in two minutes.

306
00:20:44,826 --> 00:20:46,203
- [in English] Copy, sir.
- [radio beeps]

307
00:20:46,286 --> 00:20:47,454
[in English] Copy, sir.

308
00:20:48,956 --> 00:20:49,998
[in English] Copy, sir.

309
00:20:50,082 --> 00:20:55,212
- [tense music continues]
- [radio beeps]

310
00:21:34,042 --> 00:21:38,755
[tense music continues]

311
00:22:27,804 --> 00:22:30,682
[music intensifies]

312
00:22:39,483 --> 00:22:40,233
Agent Angeles.

313
00:22:40,317 --> 00:22:42,944
Give me the coordinates
of San Aurelio Street.

314
00:22:43,028 --> 00:22:45,822
[in English] We're preparing
the digital perimeter right now.

315
00:22:45,906 --> 00:22:49,451
[in English] Task Force Alpha
is an elite team!

316
00:22:49,534 --> 00:22:51,620
[Manuel, in English]
<i>They can handle everything!</i>

317
00:22:51,703 --> 00:22:52,954
‪[sirens wailing]

318
00:22:54,039 --> 00:22:56,249
[Bennie] If anyone moves,

319
00:22:56,333 --> 00:22:57,751
I'm going to shoot her!

320
00:22:57,834 --> 00:22:59,503
Do you understand?

321
00:22:59,586 --> 00:23:03,090
<i>Don't come closer, or we'll kill them all!</i>

322
00:23:03,173 --> 00:23:04,508
[sobs]

323
00:23:04,591 --> 00:23:06,343
[in Japanese] No! Please!

324
00:23:06,426 --> 00:23:08,470
[Mr. Konno, in Japanese]
<i>My family is in there!</i>

325
00:23:08,553 --> 00:23:09,763
Keep an eye on the hostages.

326
00:23:09,846 --> 00:23:11,389
You're going to save them.

327
00:23:11,473 --> 00:23:13,308
[Marcus] <i>We'll wait</i>
<i>for Espina's go signal.</i>

328
00:23:13,391 --> 00:23:17,395
What if they planted bombs in here, too?

329
00:23:17,479 --> 00:23:20,107
[in English] Initiate a full-grid sweep
of the area! Now!

330
00:23:21,733 --> 00:23:22,859
[Espina] <i>What's their motive?</i>

331
00:23:22,943 --> 00:23:25,362
Why did they hold their clients hostage?

332
00:23:25,445 --> 00:23:28,865
- [Manuel] <i>You make sacrifices</i>
- [beeping]

333
00:23:28,949 --> 00:23:30,867
<i>for the greater good!</i>
